Orphapacket.Label: Rare disorder without a determined diagnosis after full investigation

Synonyms.Synonym: Fully investigated rare disorder without a determined diagnosis

TextSection.Contents: A rare disorder for which all reasonable efforts have been done by rare diseases experts to determine a diagnosis according to the state of the art and available diagnostic capabilities but did not enable to conclude on a clinically known concept. It is recommended to restrict the use of this entity for coding purposes to rare disease experts.

Parent.Label: Functional head of classification for rare disorder without a determined diagnosis after full investigation
